{
  "stem": "4284.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But you were always concerned about anything that you saw or heard or did to be an infraction of the rules, or as far as the Germans are concerned, breaking the law with really very serious consequences, including disappearance and not returning.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, you don't have to be told.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You were fearful on your own.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You were fearful of your own experiences.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You stepped out of the-- the house, you looked around, never knowing what you could expect.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was a sort of patriotic responsibility to beat up on Jews.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The little kids were heroes to the family, to the Nazi organization.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was an indoctrination that anything you do against the Jews was not only OK, but it was a privilege and you became a little hero.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And you would-- sometimes would have kids wait at the door, trying to beat you up to be able to go back and say, look I beat up a Jewish boy or little Jewish girl.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, but they were not of great, serious consequences.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I was not hurt.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But you were constantly shoved.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, one of the things that was really the most, it seems strange, dangerous is to go for the few privileges you had to the grocery store, where obviously, you had to buy your food with the meager earnings that my father provided.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And you were intimidated and looked upon, spat upon.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And very often, if they knew you were Jewish, you simply weren't served.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And believe me, people talk, and people let it be known, you know, that little Henry-- or Heinz, as my name was, you know-- that's that little Jewish boy from Blumenstrasse at 15, which actually, that simply said they knew your address.",
      "word_count": 42
    }
  ],
